   "author_association" : "MEMBER",
   "body" : "If the `UniqueLock()` ctor throws the \"potential deadlock detected\" exception, the object is not instantiated, and the `~UniqueLock()` dtor will never be called for it.\r\n\r\nThis behavior creates a \"ghost\" lock in the lock stack: this lock is pushed to the stack by the `UniqueLock()` ctor, but it is never popped from the stack by the `~UniqueLock()` dtor.\r\n\r\nThis PR fixes this broken behavior and improves the unit test.\r\n\r\nBug example from #19337:\r\n- https://travis-ci.org/github/bitcoin/bitcoin/jobs/700351407#L4430",
